         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nAmong the characteristics of our species, *Homo sapiens*, is the ability to walk and perform manual tasks. These characteristics did not arise from nothing; they are changes that occurred over millions of years and reached us thanks to DNA and different speciation processes — the process by which new species emerge from existing ones (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).\n\nGiven this scenario, let us reflect on the following:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b2067355-8f41-470b-a270-1de259627fc2",
                     "text": "National Geographics",
                     "page": "Speciation",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
